-- Serbia Appoints Former CEZ Representative to Lead Power Monopoly
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-09-06T12:57:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-06/serbia-appoints-former-cez-representative-to-lead-power-monopoly.html
Serbia ’s government appointed
Aleksandar Obradovic, a former representative of Czech power
utility CEZ AS in Belgrade, to head  Elektroprivreda Srbije ,
Serbia’s electricity monopoly, a government spokesman said.  Obradovic takes over from Dragomir Markovic, who was
Elektroprivreda’s general manager since March 2009, spokesman
Milivoje Mihajlovic said in a phone interview after a Cabinet
meeting today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
